  "body": "### Steps to Reproduce:\r\n1. Generate an invalid QR code (the sync code which has been already used)\r\n2. Navigate to the sync QR page using the Android\r\n3. Point the camera at the sync QR code.\r\n4. Tap the 'Try Again' button when the 'Oops something wrong' is shown\r\n5. Point the camera at the sync QR code again\r\n\r\n### Actual Result:\r\nAfter tapping the 'Try Again' button, the sync process does not proceed when the camera is pointed on the sync QR code again \r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/44b041e4-049e-4b75-bad6-2ec5840cddf7\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected Result:\r\nWhen the 'Try Again' button is tapped, the sync process should resume and attempt to sync the Android device with the QR code. \r\n\r\n### Note:\r\n The issue prevents successful syncing when the 'Try Again' button is tapped, and the sync QR page must be manually reopened\r\n\r\n### Devices:\r\n- Real device: Pixel 7a, Android 13\r\n- Real device: Huawei p20 light, Android 9\r\n\r\n### ENV:\r\nNightly [27 Jun 2023]",
